some Common Lisp implementation is likely necessary to make
use of the *.lisp code. SBCL is what I use at present, e.g.

  sbcl --script corridors.lisp

sub-directories include

    energy
      various roguelike energy (movement cost) systems.
      tl;dr -- use a "cost" or integer based energy system,
      like in Angband

    pseudo-random-dist
      make 33% odds behave more like humans think it should
      behave. or how to make searching for a hidden door not
      fail 30+ times in a row (unlikely, but possible)

the files randomly (somewhat notably?) include

    make depend
      will install any required Perl module dependencies,
      assuming perl and App::cpanminus are installed. and make.

    binpack
      makes some rectangular rooms, packs them together, and
      connects the whole lot with some doors

    caves.lisp
      lots of rectangles, randomly filled in. these may not all
      be connected

